/* uppercase identifiers and punctuation must be coded as shown.     */
/* lowercase identifiers indicate that user text needs to be coded.  */
/* < > are used to indicate that the enclosed identifiers are optnl. */
/*  |  is used to separate mutually exclusive alternatives.          */
/* { } encloses a set of alternatives, one of which must be coded.   */
/* ... denotes the preceding identifier(s) may be coded repetitively.*/
/*                                                                   */
// OPTION option<,option>...
/*                                                                   */
/* Where: option specifies one or more job control options which     */
/*               temporarily override the system defaults.  Options  */
/*               specified remain in effect for the duration of the  */
/*               job or until overriden by a contrary option.  The   */
/*               options, in any order, are as follows:              */
/*                  ACANCEL|NOACANCEL selects whether the job must be*/
/*                            canceled (instead of awaiting operator */
/*                            intervention) if an assignment (via    */
/*                            ASSGN of LIBDEF) fails.                */
/*                  ALIGN|NOALIGN selects whether the assembler is to*/
/*                            align constants & data areas on proper */
/*                            boundaries and check the alignment of  */
/*                            addresses used in machine instructions.*/
/*                  CATAL|LINK|NOLINK determines if an object module */
/*                            is link-edited or not and, if CATAL is */
/*                            specified, that the link-edited phase  */
/*                            is to be cataloged in a library.  CATAL*/
/*                            also sets the LINK option.             */
/*                  DECK|NODECK selects whether a language translator*/
/*                            is to produce an object deck on SYSPCH.*/
/*                  DUMP|PARTDUMP|NODUMP selects whether a storage   */
/*                            dump may be taken and, if so, the type */
/*                            of dump to be taken.                   */
/*                  EDECK|NOEDECK selects whether the assembler is to*/
/*                            an edited macro deck on SYSPCH for     */
/*                            cataloging in a library.               */
/*                  ERRS|NOERRS selects whether a language translator*/
/*                            will summarize all errors in the source*/
/*                            program on SYSLST.                     */
/*                  JCANCEL|NOJCANCEL selects whether the system     */
/*                            should skip to End-of-Job (instead of  */
/*                            waiting for operator intervention) if a*/
/*                            job control error occurs.              */
/*                  LIST|NOLIST selects whether a language translator*/
/*                            will produce a source listing, external*/
/*                            symbol dictionary, relocation list dic-*/
/*                            tionary, and cross-reference on SYSLST.*/
/*                  LISTX|NOLISTX selects whether the COBOL compiler */
/*                            is is to produce a PROCEDURE DIVISION  */
/*                            map on SYSLST.                         */
/*                  LOG|NOLOG selects whether all control statements */
/*                            and commands are listed on SYSLST.     */
/*                  LOGSRC|NOLOGSRC selects whether all job control  */
/*                            statements containing symbolic         */
/*                            parameters are listed twice on SYSLST: */
/*                            The first time as coded and again after*/
/*                            variable substitution has taken place. */
/*                  RLD|NORLD selects whether the assembler is to    */
/*                            produce the relocation list dictionary */
/*                            on SYSLST.  NOLIST suppresses RLD.     */
/*                  SYM|NOSYM selects whether the COBOL compiler will*/
/*                            produce a DATA DIVISION map on SYSLST. */
/*                  SYSDUMP|NOSYSDUMP selects whether dumps are to be*/
/*                            written to the dump library or SYSLST. */
/*                  TERM|NOTERM selects whether a language translator*/
/*                            will summarize all errors in the source*/
/*                            program on SYSLOG.                     */
/*                  SXREF|XREF|NOXREF determines if the assembler is */
/*                            to produce symbol cross-reference lists*/
/*                            on SYSLST and type of crossreference   */
/*                            produced.                              */
/*                                                                   */
